                <note rend="inline" type="source">325.1121 Bethune, Larry K./2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 19, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Your 21, March 18, 4 p.m. The Department reiterates the position expressed in
                    its instruction No. 604 of October 21, 1925.<note n="11" xml:id="d823fn11">See
                        footnote 10.</note> You should urgently renew your efforts with the
                    appropriate authorities to be permitted to communicate with Bethune and also
                    request a like permission for his counsel. What are the charges against him?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
